# ğŸ bug report

### Affected Package

The issue is caused by package @angular/localize

### Is this a regression?

Yes, this works in a out of the box new angular project.

### Description

Changing the value of an interpolated field does not update the displayed text when running with a locale that is not the source.
I have `en` (source) and `es` localizations with nothing different between them and the `es` messages file has `<target>` tags that match the `<source>`. 
When I run with `en`, I can click a button and change the displayed value.
When I run with `es`, I can click a button but nothing changes on the display.

Here is an example:
This is in a template
`<div class="label" (click)="click()" i18n>{{ test }}</div>`

This is the component
<pre><code>
@Component({
  selector: 'application-info-header',
  templateUrl: './application-info-header.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./application-info-header.component.scss'],
})
export class ApplicationInfoHeaderComponent implements OnInit {
  @Input()
  currentApplication: Application;

  test = false;

  click() {
    this.test = !this.test;
  }
}
</code></pre>

When I click the label with the source locale, I see the text change from False -> True -> False - etc.
When I click the label with the `es` locale, I never see the text change.

